1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,079
Jesus is coming, amen.

2
00:00:02,079 --> 00:00:03,440
What a glorious thought.

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,860
One day we'll see our Savior face-to-face,

4
00:00:05,860 --> 00:00:08,880
we'll be with Him forevermore, hallelujah.

5
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:12,600
If you're saved here this morning, that is a reality.

6
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:15,000
And I'm so thankful for that.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,440
I had somebody tell me,

8
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:18,319
actually I've had lots of people tell me this,

9
00:00:18,319 --> 00:00:20,319
you just can't know for sure

10
00:00:20,319 --> 00:00:21,760
that you're gonna go to heaven.

11
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:25,840
I mean, no one can know for sure, it's just not possible.

12
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:28,200
And sometimes someone will tell me that

13
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,559
that also tells me that they go to church.

14
00:00:30,559 --> 00:00:33,159
And they'll tell me the kind of church they go to,

15
00:00:33,159 --> 00:00:35,400
they'll tell me some things about it.

16
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,040
And so I have an opportunity at that point to say,

17
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:42,180
well, listen, do you know about a guy named Paul?

18
00:00:43,119 --> 00:00:45,400
He wrote a lot of our New Testament.

19
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,720
And they'll say, well, yeah, I heard about Paul.

20
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:52,200
Well, you know, Paul knew that he was gonna go to heaven.

21
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,580
I mean, he had confidence, he was certain,

22
00:00:54,580 --> 00:00:57,880
he said that he was ready to be offered

23
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,959
at the time of his departure was at hand.

24
00:00:59,959 --> 00:01:02,240
He knew that he was gonna receive a crown.

25
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:04,440
He said this, that it was better for him.

26
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,779
He said that he had this desire to depart,

27
00:01:06,779 --> 00:01:09,839
to be with Christ, which was far better, hallelujah.

28
00:01:09,839 --> 00:01:12,919
He knew and we can know too.

29
00:01:12,919 --> 00:01:15,879
Aren't you thankful for that this morning?

30
00:01:15,879 --> 00:01:17,959
What a blessing to be saved.

31
00:01:17,959 --> 00:01:19,559
Aren't you thankful this morning?

32
00:01:19,559 --> 00:01:21,919
If you're saved, man, you ought to rejoice,

33
00:01:21,919 --> 00:01:26,919
rejoice every single day to know that heaven is your home.

34
00:01:26,919 --> 00:01:29,120
Second Corinthians chapter number 12

35
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:31,279
and we're wrapping up our study.

36
00:01:31,279 --> 00:01:33,440
We're getting to the end of the calendar year

37
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:34,959
and therefore we're getting the end

38
00:01:34,959 --> 00:01:36,440
of the book of Second Corinthians.

39
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,400
We've been studying through Second Corinthians

40
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:42,000
on Sunday mornings all throughout 2025.

41
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,239
This is the 30th message that I've preached

42
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:46,680
here from Second Corinthians to say,

43
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:48,160
would you preach the other weeks?

44
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:50,559
Well, from other portions of scripture,

45
00:01:50,559 --> 00:01:52,459
someone asked me last week, pastor,

46
00:01:52,459 --> 00:01:54,720
why aren't you preaching from Second Corinthians?

47
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,239
Because the Holy Spirit told me

48
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:58,400
to preach from somewhere else, amen.

49
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,519
And I want to obey the Lord.

50
00:02:00,519 --> 00:02:02,879
And so we dealt with a different passage last week,

51
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:06,059
but here we are back in Second Corinthians chapter 12.

52
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:09,160
And it's been a wonderful study, our theme all year,

53
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:12,119
God's grace is sufficient.

54
00:02:12,119 --> 00:02:16,960
I hope, I pray that you have experienced that truth

55
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:20,740
afresh, anew in your life here in 2025,

56
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:22,979
that God's grace is sufficient.

57
00:02:22,979 --> 00:02:25,380
And what a blessed promise that is.

58
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:27,419
It's not only a promise that's explained to us

59
00:02:27,419 --> 00:02:29,419
in God's word, but it's a promise

60
00:02:29,419 --> 00:02:31,779
that every child of God must embrace

61
00:02:31,779 --> 00:02:34,020
in their personal life to know

62
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:36,979
that God's grace is sufficient.

63
00:02:36,979 --> 00:02:39,440
Last time we were in Second Corinthians,

64
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:42,820
we were looking at verses 11 down through verse number 19.

65
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:44,380
And in that portion of scripture,

66
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:47,419
we talked about Paul's love for the Corinthians.

67
00:02:47,419 --> 00:02:49,699
We're reminded that the Lord Jesus Christ,

68
00:02:49,699 --> 00:02:51,500
before he went to the cross of Calvary,

69
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,820
would meet with his disciples

70
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:55,380
and he would tell them at the end of the 13th chapter

71
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:57,860
of the book of John, that he gave them a new commandment.

72
00:02:57,860 --> 00:02:59,940
And that new commandment was that they love one another

73
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:03,460
as Christ loved them, that's how they were to love.

74
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:06,580
And he said, by this, by your love one for another,

75
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:09,380
shall all men know that you're my disciples.

76
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,940
We find that the apostle Paul would encourage the church

77
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:14,660
at Thessalonica with regard to this truth

78
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:15,699
of brotherly love.

79
00:03:15,699 --> 00:03:17,059
And he said, you already know this,

80
00:03:17,059 --> 00:03:19,699
you're already doing this, but I wanna beg you,

81
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:24,380
I wanna encourage you to increase more and more.

82
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:26,380
And in this particular passage,

83
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,100
Paul is sharing with the believers in Corinth,

84
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,899
reminding them of his love for them.

85
00:03:31,899 --> 00:03:36,300
He says that the more he loved, that the less he was loved.

86
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,020
But it didn't stop him from loving.

87
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:40,259
He loved them as Christ loved.

88
00:03:40,259 --> 00:03:44,240
And we said this, it is impossible for us to love

89
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:47,660
as we're supposed to love if we're not filled

90
00:03:47,660 --> 00:03:49,660
with the Holy Spirit of God.

91
00:03:50,619 --> 00:03:53,860
Because the Holy Spirit, the Bible tells us

92
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:55,940
that the fruit of the Spirit is love.

93
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:58,220
The first one that's mentioned there, love.

94
00:03:58,220 --> 00:04:01,500
And we understand the Holy Spirit who indwells us

95
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,820
as we're filled with the Holy Spirit,

96
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:06,820
that he allows us to love as Christ loved.

97
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:09,860
And we're to love one another, and I'm thankful for that.

98
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:12,740
As we look at the end of chapter number 12,

99
00:04:12,740 --> 00:04:16,459
we find that the apostle Paul is going to deal

100
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,579
with something that is absolutely essential

101
00:04:19,579 --> 00:04:23,100
to be dealt with, and he deals with it in love.

102
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:26,140
Notice in verse number 20, in 2 Corinthians 12,

103
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,540
in verse 20, the Bible says this,

104
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:31,700
"'For I fear, lest when I come,

105
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,540
I shall not find you such as I would,

106
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:39,260
and that I should be found unto you such as you would not,

107
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:44,059
lest there be debates, envyings, wraths,

108
00:04:44,059 --> 00:04:48,540
strifes, backbitings, whisperings,

109
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:51,459
swellings, tumults.'"

110
00:04:51,459 --> 00:04:54,299
Verse 21, "'And lest when I come again,

111
00:04:54,299 --> 00:04:56,380
my God will humble me among you,

112
00:04:56,380 --> 00:05:01,299
and that I shall bewail many which have sinned already

113
00:05:01,299 --> 00:05:06,019
and have not repented of the uncleanness and fornication

114
00:05:06,019 --> 00:05:10,739
and lasciviousness which they have committed.'"

115
00:05:10,739 --> 00:05:12,899
As we look at these two verses of Scripture,

116
00:05:12,899 --> 00:05:15,660
I've simply titled the message this morning,

117
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:19,420
Sin Must Be Addressed.

118
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:23,260
For the last three weeks, Dean has selected a song

119
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:26,220
that goes so well with either a morning message

120
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:28,899
or an evening message, and it's so neat

121
00:05:28,899 --> 00:05:30,540
to see how the Holy Spirit works.

122
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:34,220
I mentioned two weeks ago when that happened

123
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:35,700
that it was neat to see the Holy Spirit.

124
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:36,980
Last week on Sunday night,

125
00:05:36,980 --> 00:05:39,179
I said that Dean's looking at my sermon notes.

126
00:05:39,179 --> 00:05:41,459
He's coming into the office and he's checking my notes

127
00:05:41,459 --> 00:05:44,260
and he's picking the songs, which he's really not.

128
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,500
But we sang last week,

129
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:47,899
How Great Thou Art in the evening service.

130
00:05:47,899 --> 00:05:51,059
And then we spoke, we preached about the greatness of God.

131
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,779
Only God is great.

132
00:05:52,779 --> 00:05:53,980
That was the title of my message.

133
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:56,779
And we just got done singing, How Great Thou Art.

134
00:05:56,779 --> 00:05:57,619
It's so awesome.

135
00:05:57,619 --> 00:06:00,140
Well, this morning, Sin Must Be Addressed.

136
00:06:00,140 --> 00:06:02,420
And if you remember not the special song,

137
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:04,459
but the last hymn that we sang

138
00:06:04,459 --> 00:06:06,619
as a congregation this morning,

139
00:06:06,619 --> 00:06:11,619
Nothing Between My Soul and My Savior.

140
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:17,140
What an appropriate song to lead into a message

141
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:20,339
that as we look at verse 20 and 21 of 2 Corinthians 12,

142
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:23,459
that sin must be dealt with.

143
00:06:23,459 --> 00:06:26,299
We find in verse 20 that he speaks about their carnality.

144
00:06:26,299 --> 00:06:28,739
And he mentions a whole list of things

145
00:06:28,739 --> 00:06:29,940
there at the end of the verse

146
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:32,220
and really representing the carnality.

147
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:34,299
We know much about the church in Corinth.

148
00:06:34,299 --> 00:06:37,739
We know some of the things from the first book

149
00:06:37,739 --> 00:06:39,200
that Paul writes to them.

150
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:41,700
But I want you to be mindful of this this morning,

151
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,899
that believers, those that have trusted

152
00:06:43,899 --> 00:06:47,019
the Lord Jesus Christ as their personal savior

153
00:06:47,019 --> 00:06:49,820
have this wonderful promise that we read

154
00:06:49,820 --> 00:06:51,739
in Romans 6 and verse 14.

155
00:06:51,739 --> 00:06:56,739
And it's this, that sin shall not have dominion over you.

156
00:06:57,339 --> 00:06:58,859
That's a precious promise

157
00:06:58,859 --> 00:07:01,540
that God has given to his children.

158
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:04,100
If you're saved, you've been delivered

159
00:07:04,899 --> 00:07:06,700
from the penalty of sin.

160
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:07,540
Amen?

161
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:10,220
For the wages of sin is death,

162
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:12,980
but the gift of God is eternal life

163
00:07:12,980 --> 00:07:15,339
through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

164
00:07:15,339 --> 00:07:16,899
And if you're saved this morning,

165
00:07:16,899 --> 00:07:20,059
if you've trusted Jesus Christ as your personal savior,

166
00:07:20,059 --> 00:07:23,179
then you've been delivered from the penalty of sin.

167
00:07:23,179 --> 00:07:26,700
However, I believe that you've also discovered

168
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:29,019
that you still have the old nature,

169
00:07:30,339 --> 00:07:33,140
the flesh, the old man.

170
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:36,540
And you find that you still sin, right?

171
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:38,059
We look at the book of Ephesians,

172
00:07:38,059 --> 00:07:39,459
we look at the book of Colossians,

173
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:40,940
and in both of those books,

174
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:44,660
the apostle Paul is writing to saved people.

175
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:46,420
And as he's writing to those saved people,

176
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:50,820
he gives them the principle of putting off the old

177
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:52,820
and putting on the new.

178
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:56,480
And we find that sin no longer has dominion over us.

179
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,220
We're saved, we're saved from the penalty of sin,

180
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:02,600
but we still have this old flesh, the old nature.

181
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,640
The Bible says that if you walk in the spirit,

182
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:08,519
you shall not fulfill the lust of the flesh.

183
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:11,399
It did not say that your flesh would not lust.

184
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,640
How many of you would like it if that's the way it worked?

185
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:17,440
It doesn't work that way

186
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:20,119
because God wants us to walk in the spirit.

187
00:08:21,239 --> 00:08:23,760
And he says, it's a wonderful promise in Galatians 5,

188
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,760
if you walk in the spirit,

189
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:29,320
you shall not fulfill the lust of the flesh.

190
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:32,760
And we find this morning that the church in Corinth,

191
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:35,280
the apostle Paul expresses concern

192
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:37,280
here in these verses of scripture.

193
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,039
And we could look at this this morning

194
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:43,140
and understand that if you're not saved,

195
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:47,159
you have a sin debt that will send you to the lake of fire.

196
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:49,359
If you're not saved this morning,

197
00:08:49,359 --> 00:08:52,080
you've never trusted the Lord Jesus Christ

198
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,440
as your personal savior,

199
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:56,140
you've never received the gift of God,

200
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,960
that means that you are condemned.

201
00:08:59,599 --> 00:09:00,979
So what the Bible says,

202
00:09:00,979 --> 00:09:04,039
the Bible says that you're condemned already.

203
00:09:04,039 --> 00:09:05,559
And it's because of our sin,

204
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:10,520
the wages of sin is death for all have sinned

205
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:13,080
and come short of the glory of God.

206
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,200
And if you're lost this morning,

207
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,359
the sin that you must deal with is being saved

208
00:09:18,359 --> 00:09:21,359
and allowing for the precious blood of Christ

209
00:09:21,359 --> 00:09:23,320
to be placed upon your account.

210
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:26,760
We would look at the truth of earlier in this book,

211
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,559
2 Corinthians 5 and verse 21,

212
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:32,880
for he God hath made him Jesus to be sin for us

213
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:35,520
who knew no sin that we might be made

214
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:38,000
the righteousness of God in him.

215
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,559
We would use the term imputed righteousness.

216
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:44,280
And that's when the righteousness of God

217
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:47,479
is placed on your account and my account

218
00:09:47,479 --> 00:09:49,280
at the moment of salvation,

219
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,520
and we're declared righteous,

220
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:55,200
we're saved from the penalty of sin.

221
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:58,000
And if you're here this morning and you're still lost,

222
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
you've never trusted Jesus Christ.

223
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,839
as your personal Savior.

224
00:10:00,839 --> 00:10:02,339
Can I tell you this morning,

225
00:10:02,339 --> 00:10:04,880
today is the day of salvation.

226
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:07,380
Can I tell you what Jesus said to Nicodemus?

227
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:09,000
He was a religious leader.

228
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,760
He was a man that knew a lot about God,

229
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:13,340
but he didn't know God.

230
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:16,719
He was a man that tried to keep all kinds of rules

231
00:10:16,719 --> 00:10:19,180
and regulations, but Jesus said to him,

232
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:22,059
ye must be born again.

233
00:10:23,139 --> 00:10:24,940
Religion can't save you.

234
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,739
Only Christ can save you.

235
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:30,319
Your good works can't save you.

236
00:10:30,319 --> 00:10:32,819
Only Christ can save you.

237
00:10:32,819 --> 00:10:36,740
And we can rejoice this morning in salvation,

238
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,279
but then we must understand,

239
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:41,200
listen, there's a false teaching that's prevalent today.

240
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:43,360
It's called antinomianism,

241
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:45,880
and it has this idea that you're saved,

242
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,220
and therefore you can just live however you wanna live,

243
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:51,000
because you're saved, you're going to heaven.

244
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,240
The Bible tells us in the book of Galatians

245
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,840
that we're not to use our liberty

246
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:57,099
for an occasion to the flesh.

247
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,119
And what we find this morning is that,

248
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:03,580
yes, I'm saved and I'm going to heaven,

249
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:06,120
and I can't do anything to keep my salvation.

250
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,220
I'm kept by the power of God.

251
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,180
He saved me.

252
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:10,180
He keeps me.

253
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:11,019
Hallelujah.

254
00:11:11,019 --> 00:11:12,220
Praise God.

255
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,919
But I am to walk worthy.

256
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:18,500
I am to live a life that is pleasing to God,

257
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,819
and we find that throughout the New Testament,

258
00:11:20,819 --> 00:11:24,800
there's many references with regard to dealing with sin

259
00:11:25,639 --> 00:11:26,739
in the life of a believer,

260
00:11:27,739 --> 00:11:29,879
